{Ph Correction}
Water from upland reservoirs is usually acidic and this acidity is slightly increased by the effect of alum and chlorine. To neutralise this acidity and to redue the corrosive propeties of the water, lime is added after filtration.
Although the lime reduces the corrosive properties of the water, it can never be totally non-corrosive. To protect the water mains from the effects of this water, sodium silicate is added. Sodium silicate forms a protective layer on the inner surface of iron mains thus reducing corrosion.
